    - "Revised intent-clarity reasoning to name all three unresolved design forks (bash-vs-Python; REPO_ROOT/CORTEX_COMMAND_ROOT/$PYTHONPATH semantics under uv tool install -e; orchestrator-round prompt template path classification) rather than calling one 'secondary'."
    - "Added to intent-clarity reasoning that the CLI surface itself has unspecified edges: cancel's 116 dependency and logs cursor protocol are undefined."
    - "Revised scope-boundedness reasoning to note that CORTEX_COMMAND_ROOT/$PYTHONPATH sites and test-migration scope are un-inventoried, and that out-of-scope carve-outs are not clean (cancel invokes 116-owned infrastructure; dashboard reads runner-written state files)."
    - "Revised requirements-alignment rating from HIGH to Partial. Ticket preserves three named must-haves but does not enumerate the full pipeline.md preservation surface (zero-merge PR draft + [ZERO PROGRESS], integration_pr_flipped_once, --dry-run + test_runner_pr_gating.py, post-merge sync, conflict fast-path, deferral schema, rework cycles). Research must surface these as preservation requirements."
    - "Removed the project.md day/night-philosophy anchor from the alignment reasoning as orthogonal to what this ticket changes."
    - "Flagged --dry-run + test_runner_pr_gating.py as a direct pipeline.md conflict. Resolved as a scope refinement: the --dry-run contract and its test are in-scope preservation requirements; the migration mechanism follows from the bash-vs-Python design fork resolution."
    - "Added explicit complexity/criticality reasoning grounded in the ~11,000 LOC rebuild scale, pipeline.md's seven must-have blocks, and project.md's framing of overnight as the core autonomous-execution capability. Complexity: complex. Criticality: critical."
  dismissals:
